From e4f13af2fe02d1ec6dba672c7ba4433a04a65ec7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Fri, 8 May 2026 15:16:21 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Phase 10 follow-up: Approve / Comment / Request Changes
 verdicts on submit
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Submit Review now opens a two-step dialog: first a three-button
prompt for the verdict (Comment, Approve, Request changes) and then
an input dialog for the optional summary body. The dialog primitives
don't support input + multi-button in one pass, so we lean on prompt
for verdict selection and follow up with input for the body.

The chosen `ReviewSubmissionEvent` flows through the existing draft
service → provider path; `submitReview` already accepted all three
events. Notification copy adapts to the verdict ("Approved",
"Requested changes", "Review posted"). Body-input dialog message and
primary button copy adapt too so the user can confirm the verdict
before committing.
